{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/gallstones/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"6a20e318-0a3a-5ca9-af4d-e296bbd19df0","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 6fa5c717-a5cd-432b-be07-a7f2018981be --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 6fa5c717-a5cd-432b-be07-a7f2018981be -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 84d70fcd-ee0b-4ca2-acd7-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 88d4cc1b-2b41-4b15-a61f-a7f2018981be --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 88d4cc1b-2b41-4b15-a61f-a7f2018981be --><!-- begin field 5e4c16a4-3a30-4da4-84f5-a7f2018981be --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 5e4c16a4-3a30-4da4-84f5-a7f2018981be --><!-- begin field a861434e-ddd5-4e30-9175-a7f2018981be --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field a861434e-ddd5-4e30-9175-a7f2018981be --><!-- begin field 6b883fe2-eb11-4dc4-9eb0-a7f2018981be --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 6b883fe2-eb11-4dc4-9eb0-a7f2018981be --><!-- begin field 1beaf9c0-6d14-4656-b862-a7f2018981be --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 1beaf9c0-6d14-4656-b862-a7f2018981be --><!-- begin field 4f57c06d-d7d4-4a1a-99eb-a7f2018981be --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 4f57c06d-d7d4-4a1a-99eb-a7f2018981be --><!-- end item 84d70fcd-ee0b-4ca2-acd7-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"b39f129d-317e-5f6f-8d43-a4b23ddcb2e8","topicId":"b66a5697-882a-4143-a0c6-32b03657c794","topicName":"Gallstones","slug":"gallstones","lastRevised":"Last revised in JuneÂ 2019","chapters":[{"id":"06a059af-2d68-5ae7-8e88-57f00c6cdb2f","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e0f409fd-998f-5b21-9f3a-5f11ad52d70f","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9db03e94-e4f9-5d18-bd20-c911b8c565e7","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"83aa8167-37ee-5580-b667-eeed0c3c6864","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"e4b85e87-e2a9-57ce-846e-56d02c965e49","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"646754ea-ab1a-5659-bc5e-90394d1f97b8","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"c619902d-f978-51b5-809a-8b8236aefac7","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"5d3a306f-2228-5592-8a4e-035ea7b6849c","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"6070d034-6424-5a50-bc71-08f38595f3f0","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"